 Sacked Kano Commissioner of Works and Infrastructural developments, Engineer Muazu Magaji, has been discharged after recovering from coronavirus. He announced this on his Facebook timeline. According to him: “To the Glory of Allah SWT, today Friday 22nd May and 29th Ramadan I have been confirmed Covid-19 negative and discharged from Isolation centre.” Magaji was relieved of his appointment for celebrating the death of late Chief of staff to the President, Abba Kyari. Governor Umar Ganduje on April 18 sacked Mu’azu Magaji for making indecent comments over the death of Kyari. He tested positive for COVID-19 on May 7.